channel.title: Papers with Code: Latest (unofficial)
channel.description: As a disclaimer, this is an unofficial feed and has no affiliation with Papers with Code.

item.title: Multi-source Semantic Graph-based Multimodal Sarcasm Explanation Generation
item.description: Multimodal Sarcasm Explanation (MuSE) is a new yet challenging task, which aims to generate a natural language sentence for a multimodal social post (an image as well as its caption) to explain why it contains sarcasm.

item.title: Unsupervised 3D registration through optimization-guided cyclical self-training
item.description: State-of-the-art deep learning-based registration methods employ three different learning strategies: supervised learning, which requires costly manual annotations, unsupervised learning, which heavily relies on hand-crafted similarity metrics designed by domain experts, or learning from synthetic data, which introduces a domain shift.

item.title: Detect Any Deepfakes: Segment Anything Meets Face Forgery Detection and Localization
item.description: The rapid advancements in computer vision have stimulated remarkable progress in face forgery techniques, capturing the dedicated attention of researchers committed to detecting forgeries and precisely localizing manipulated areas.

item.title: MNISQ: A Large-Scale Quantum Circuit Dataset for Machine Learning on/for Quantum Computers in the NISQ era
item.description: In fact, also the Machine Learning research related to quantum computers undertakes a dual challenge: enhancing machine learning exploiting the power of quantum computers, while also leveraging state-of-the-art classical machine learning methodologies to help the advancement of quantum computing.

item.title: NaturalInversion: Data-Free Image Synthesis Improving Real-World Consistency
item.description: We introduce NaturalInversion, a novel model inversion-based method to synthesize images that agrees well with the original data distribution without using real data.

item.title: BinaryViT: Pushing Binary Vision Transformers Towards Convolutional Models
item.description: With the increasing popularity and the increasing size of vision transformers (ViTs), there has been an increasing interest in making them more efficient and less computationally costly for deployment on edge devices with limited computing resources.

item.title: SimPLe: Similarity-Aware Propagation Learning for Weakly-Supervised Breast Cancer Segmentation in DCE-MRI
item.description: The network first utilizes the pseudo-masks generated using the extreme points to train itself, by minimizing a contrastive loss, which encourages the network to learn more representative features for cancerous voxels.

item.title: Foundation Model for Endoscopy Video Analysis via Large-scale Self-supervised Pre-train
item.description: Foundation models have exhibited remarkable success in various applications, such as disease diagnosis and text report generation.

item.title: Medoid splits for efficient random forests in metric spaces
item.description: This paper revisits an adaptation of the random forest algorithm for Fr\'echet regression, addressing the challenge of regression in the context of random objects in metric spaces.

item.title: Tokenization and the Noiseless Channel
item.description: Subword tokenization is a key part of many NLP pipelines.

item.title: BEDLAM: A Synthetic Dataset of Bodies Exhibiting Detailed Lifelike Animated Motion
item.description: BEDLAM is useful for a variety of tasks and all images, ground truth bodies, 3D clothing, support code, and more are available for research purposes.

item.title: Beyond CO2 Emissions: The Overlooked Impact of Water Consumption of Information Retrieval Models
item.description: As in other fields of artificial intelligence, the information retrieval community has grown interested in investigating the power consumption associated with neural models, particularly models of search.

item.title: Computationally Assisted Quality Control for Public Health Data Streams
item.description: However, existing outlier detection frameworks perform poorly on this task because they do not account for the data volume or for the statistical properties of public health streams.

item.title: Provable Advantage of Curriculum Learning on Parity Targets with Mixed Inputs
item.description: Experimental results have shown that curriculum learning, i. e., presenting simpler examples before more complex ones, can improve the efficiency of learning.

item.title: ManimML: Communicating Machine Learning Architectures with Animation
item.description: A user can take a preexisting neural network architecture and easily write a specification for an animation in ManimML, which will then automatically compose animations for different components of the system into a final animation of the entire neural network.

item.title: PCDAL: A Perturbation Consistency-Driven Active Learning Approach for Medical Image Segmentation and Classification
item.description: To address this limitation, we propose an AL-based method that can be simultaneously applied to 2D medical image classification, segmentation, and 3D medical image segmentation tasks.

item.title: Comparison of Single- and Multi- Objective Optimization Quality for Evolutionary Equation Discovery
item.description: Evolutionary differential equation discovery proved to be a tool to obtain equations with less a priori assumptions than conventional approaches, such as sparse symbolic regression over the complete possible terms library.

item.title: The Drunkard's Odometry: Estimating Camera Motion in Deforming Scenes
item.description: Estimating camera motion in deformable scenes poses a complex and open research challenge.

item.title: Numerical Data Imputation for Multimodal Data Sets: A Probabilistic Nearest-Neighbor Kernel Density Approach
item.description: We compare our method with previous data imputation methods using artificial and real-world data with different data missing scenarios and various data missing rates, and show that our method can cope with complex original data structure, yields lower data imputation errors, and provides probabilistic estimates with higher likelihood than current methods.

item.title: Safe Model-Based Multi-Agent Mean-Field Reinforcement Learning
item.description: Many applications, e. g., in shared mobility, require coordinating a large number of agents.

item.title: On the Relationship Between RNN Hidden State Vectors and Semantic Ground Truth
item.description: We examine the assumption that the hidden-state vectors of recurrent neural networks (RNNs) tend to form clusters of semantically similar vectors, which we dub the clustering hypothesis.

item.title: Would I have gotten that reward? Long-term credit assignment by counterfactual contribution analysis
item.description: We show that measuring contributions w. r. t.

item.title: ZeroGen: Zero-shot Multimodal Controllable Text Generation with Multiple Oracles
item.description: Automatically generating textual content with desired attributes is an ambitious task that people have pursued long.

item.title: NAUTILUS: boosting Bayesian importance nested sampling with deep learning
item.description: We introduce a novel approach to boost the efficiency of the importance nested sampling (INS) technique for Bayesian posterior and evidence estimation using deep learning.

item.title: Graph Sampling-based Meta-Learning for Molecular Property Prediction
item.description: To effectively utilize many-to-many correlations of molecules and properties, we propose a Graph Sampling-based Meta-learning (GS-Meta) framework for few-shot molecular property prediction.

item.title: Macro Placement by Wire-Mask-Guided Black-Box Optimization
item.description: WireMask-BBO has the potential to significantly improve the quality and efficiency of chip floorplanning, which makes it appealing to researchers and practitioners in EDA and will also promote the application of BBO.

item.title: Ducho: A Unified Framework for the Extraction of Multimodal Features in Recommendation
item.description: Motivated by the outlined aspects, we propose Ducho, a unified framework for the extraction of multimodal features in recommendation.

item.title: RL4CO: an Extensive Reinforcement Learning for Combinatorial Optimization Benchmark
item.description: We hope RL4CO will encourage the exploration of novel solutions to complex real-world tasks, allowing to compare with existing methods through a standardized interface that decouples the science from the software engineering.

item.title: Alternative Telescopic Displacement: An Efficient Multimodal Alignment Method
item.description: Feature alignment is the primary means of fusing multimodal data.

item.title: MIS-FM: 3D Medical Image Segmentation using Foundation Models Pretrained on a Large-Scale Unannotated Dataset
item.description: The proposed model was pretrained with 110k unannotated 3D CT volumes, and experiments with different downstream segmentation targets including head and neck organs, thoracic/abdominal organs showed that our pretrained model largely outperformed training from scratch and several state-of-the-art self-supervised training methods and segmentation models.

item.title: MEMD-ABSA: A Multi-Element Multi-Domain Dataset for Aspect-Based Sentiment Analysis
item.description: Aspect-based sentiment analysis is a long-standing research interest in the field of opinion mining, and in recent years, researchers have gradually shifted their focus from simple ABSA subtasks to end-to-end multi-element ABSA tasks.

item.title: NeuralFuse: Learning to Improve the Accuracy of Access-Limited Neural Network Inference in Low-Voltage Regimes
item.description: To address this challenge, we introduce NeuralFuse, a novel add-on module that addresses the accuracy-energy tradeoff in low-voltage regimes by learning input transformations to generate error-resistant data representations.

item.title: Exploring the Representation Power of SPLADE Models
item.description: The SPLADE (SParse Lexical AnD Expansion) model is a highly effective approach to learned sparse retrieval, where documents are represented by term impact scores derived from large language models.

item.title: Predicting Music Hierarchies with a Graph-Based Neural Decoder
item.description: This paper describes a data-driven framework to parse musical sequences into dependency trees, which are hierarchical structures used in music cognition research and music analysis.

item.title: Surgical Phase and Instrument Recognition: How to identify appropriate Dataset Splits
item.description: Purpose: The development of machine learning models for surgical workflow and instrument recognition from temporal data represents a challenging task due to the complex nature of surgical workflows.

item.title: End-to-end Autonomous Driving: Challenges and Frontiers
item.description: The autonomous driving community has witnessed a rapid growth in approaches that embrace an end-to-end algorithm framework, utilizing raw sensor input to generate vehicle motion plans, instead of concentrating on individual tasks such as detection and motion prediction.

item.title: Self-Supervised MRI Reconstruction with Unrolled Diffusion Models
item.description: Magnetic Resonance Imaging (MRI) produces excellent soft tissue contrast, albeit it is an inherently slow imaging modality.

item.title: On the Predictive Accuracy of Neural Temporal Point Process Models for Continuous-time Event Data
item.description: To bridge this gap, we present a comprehensive large-scale experimental study that systematically evaluates the predictive accuracy of state-of-the-art neural TPP models.

item.title: Improving Time and Memory Efficiency of Genetic Algorithms by Storing Populations as Minimum Spanning Trees of Patches
item.description: In many applications of evolutionary algorithms the computational cost of applying operators and storing populations is comparable to the cost of fitness evaluation.

item.title: Assessing the Performance of 1D-Convolution Neural Networks to Predict Concentration of Mixture Components from Raman Spectra
item.description: Finding the optimal algorithm for a specific bioreactor environment is challenging due to the lack of freely available Raman mixture datasets.

item.title: Mitigating the Accuracy-Robustness Trade-off via Multi-Teacher Adversarial Distillation
item.description: Adversarial training is a practical approach for improving the robustness of deep neural networks against adversarial attacks.

item.title: A Framework for Identifying Depression on Social Media: MentalRiskES@IberLEF 2023
item.description: This paper describes our participation in the MentalRiskES task at IberLEF 2023.

item.title: Neural directional distance field object representation for uni-directional path-traced rendering
item.description: Faster rendering of synthetic images is a core problem in the field of computer graphics.

item.title: Palm: Predicting Actions through Language Models @ Ego4D Long-Term Action Anticipation Challenge 2023
item.description: We present Palm, a solution to the Long-Term Action Anticipation (LTA) task utilizing vision-language and large language models.

item.title: Distributional Modeling for Location-Aware Adversarial Patches
item.description: In this paper, we propose the Distribution-Optimized Adversarial Patch (DOPatch), a novel method that optimizes a multimodal distribution of adversarial locations instead of individual ones.

item.title: S2SNet: A Pretrained Neural Network for Superconductivity Discovery
item.description: To the best of our knowledge, S2SNet is the first work to predict superconductivity with only information of crystal structures.

item.title: Most Language Models can be Poets too: An AI Writing Assistant and Constrained Text Generation Studio
item.description: We present a simple and universally applicable technique for modifying the output of a language model by compositionally applying filter functions to the language models vocabulary before a unit of text is generated.

item.title: Dynamic Path-Controllable Deep Unfolding Network for Compressive Sensing
item.description: Deep unfolding network (DUN) that unfolds the optimization algorithm into a deep neural network has achieved great success in compressive sensing (CS) due to its good interpretability and high performance.

item.title: MultiZoo & MultiBench: A Standardized Toolkit for Multimodal Deep Learning
item.description: Learning multimodal representations involves integrating information from multiple heterogeneous sources of data.

item.title: Empirical Loss Landscape Analysis of Neural Network Activation Functions
item.description: Activation functions play a significant role in neural network design by enabling non-linearity.
